sql:
SELECT oi.order_item_id, ps.product_size_id, oi.product_id, oi.size_detail_id
FROM order_items oi
INNER JOIN product_sizes ps ON oi.product_id = ps.product_id AND oi.size_detail_id = ps.size_detail_id;

external_knowledge:
- Specific client refers to customer_id = 1;
- Different items denote unique product_id entries;
- Purchased implies orders placed by the customer.

- The "first fruits of the season were harvested" on September 2, 2023;
- "Gardeners planted more than one seed" refers to products with a quantity greater than one;
- The "most beloved flower" is represented by product ID 1 in the database;
- The metaphor of "explorers and their voyages" is used to describe the order IDs and customer IDs.

sql:
SELECT o.total_cost, o.currency, oi.product_id, oi.size_detail_id 
FROM orders o 
INNER JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id;

SELECT * 
FROM order_items 
WHERE (product_id, size_detail_id) NOT IN (SELECT product_id, size_detail_id FROM product_sizes);

SELECT product_id, size_detail_id, SUM(quantity) AS total_quantity
FROM order_items
GROUP BY product_id, size_detail_id;

SELECT size_detail_id 
FROM order_items 
WHERE order_id = 1;
